{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Cultural evolution is a dangerous child"},{"time":3000,"text":"for any species to let loose on its planet."},{"time":6000,"text":"By the time you realize what's happening, the child is a toddler,"},{"time":10000,"text":"up and causing havoc, and it's too late to put it back."},{"time":16000,"text":"We humans are Earth's Pandoran species."},{"time":19000,"text":"We're the ones who let the second replicator out of its box,"},{"time":24000,"text":"and we can't push it back in."},{"time":26000,"text":"We're seeing the consequences all around us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30000,"text":"Now that, I suggest, is the view that"},{"time":34000,"text":"comes out of taking memetics seriously."},{"time":36000,"text":"And it gives us a new way of thinking about"},{"time":38000,"text":"not only what's going on on our planet,"},{"time":40000,"text":"but what might be going on elsewhere in the cosmos."},{"time":43000,"text":"So first of all, I'd like to say something about memetics"},{"time":46000,"text":"and the theory of memes,"},{"time":48000,"text":"and secondly, how this might answer questions about who's out there,"},{"time":53000,"text":"if indeed anyone is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56000,"text":"So, memetics:"},{"time":58000,"text":"memetics is founded on the principle of Universal Darwinism."},{"time":62000,"text":"Darwin had this amazing idea."},{"time":65000,"text":"Indeed, some people say"},{"time":67000,"text":"it's the best idea anybody ever had."},{"time":70000,"text":"Isn't that a wonderful thought, that there could be such a thing"},{"time":74000,"text":"as a best idea anybody ever had?"},{"time":76000,"text":"Do you think there could?"},{"time":77000,"text":"Audience: No."},{"time":78000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":79000,"text":"Susan Blackmore: Someone says no, very loudly, from over there."},{"time":81000,"text":"Well, I say yes, and if there is, I give the prize to Darwin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85000,"text":"Why?"},{"time":87000,"text":"Because the idea was so simple,"},{"time":90000,"text":"and yet it explains all design in the universe."},{"time":96000,"text":"I would say not just biological design,"},{"time":98000,"text":"but all of the design that we think of as human design."},{"time":100000,"text":"It's all just the same thing happening."},{"time":102000,"text":"What did Darwin say?"},{"time":104000,"text":"I know you know the idea, natural selection,"},{"time":106000,"text":"but let me just paraphrase \"The Origin of Species,\" 1859,"},{"time":111000,"text":"in a few sentences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113000,"text":"What Darwin said was something like this:"},{"time":116000,"text":"if you have creatures that vary, and that can't be doubted --"},{"time":120000,"text":"I've been to the Galapagos, and I've measured the size of the beaks"},{"time":123000,"text":"and the size of the turtle shells and so on, and so on."},{"time":125000,"text":"And 100 pages later."},{"time":127000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":129000,"text":"And if there is a struggle for life,"},{"time":133000,"text":"such that nearly all of these creatures die --"},{"time":136000,"text":"and this can't be doubted, I've read Malthus"},{"time":139000,"text":"and I've calculated how long it would take for elephants"},{"time":141000,"text":"to cover the whole world if they bred unrestricted, and so on and so on."},{"time":144000,"text":"And another 100 pages later."},{"time":148000,"text":"And if the very few that survive pass onto their offspring"},{"time":153000,"text":"whatever it was that helped them survive,"},{"time":156000,"text":"then those offspring must be better adapted"},{"time":158000,"text":"to the circumstances in which all this happened"},{"time":160000,"text":"than their parents were."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163000,"text":"You see the idea?"},{"time":165000,"text":"If, if, if, then."},{"time":167000,"text":"He had no concept of the idea of an algorithm,"},{"time":169000,"text":"but that's what he described in that book,"},{"time":172000,"text":"and this is what we now know as the evolutionary algorithm."},{"time":175000,"text":"The principle is you just need those three things --"},{"time":179000,"text":"variation, selection and heredity."},{"time":182000,"text":"And as Dan Dennett puts it, if you have those,"},{"time":186000,"text":"then you must get evolution."},{"time":188000,"text":"Or design out of chaos, without the aid of mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193000,"text":"There's one word I love on that slide."},{"time":195000,"text":"What do you think my favorite word is?"},{"time":197000,"text":"Audience: Chaos."},{"time":198000,"text":"SB: Chaos? No. What? Mind? No."},{"time":201000,"text":"Audience: Without."},{"time":202000,"text":"SB: No, not without."},{"time":203000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":204000,"text":"You try them all in order: Mmm...?"},{"time":206000,"text":"Audience: Must."},{"time":207000,"text":"SB: Must, at must. Must, must."},{"time":211000,"text":"This is what makes it so amazing."},{"time":213000,"text":"You don't need a designer,"},{"time":216000,"text":"or a plan, or foresight, or anything else."},{"time":219000,"text":"If there's something that is copied with variation"},{"time":222000,"text":"and it's selected, then you must get design appearing out of nowhere."},{"time":226000,"text":"You can't stop it."},{"time":228000,"text":"Must is my favorite word there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233000,"text":"Now, what's this to do with memes?"},{"time":235000,"text":"Well, the principle here applies to anything"},{"time":240000,"text":"that is copied with variation and selection."},{"time":241000,"text":"We're so used to thinking in terms of biology,"},{"time":244000,"text":"we think about genes this way."},{"time":246000,"text":"Darwin didn't, of course; he didn't know about genes."},{"time":249000,"text":"He talked mostly about animals and plants,"},{"time":251000,"text":"but also about languages evolving and becoming extinct."},{"time":254000,"text":"But the principle of Universal Darwinism"},{"time":256000,"text":"is that any information that is varied and selected"},{"time":260000,"text":"will produce design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262000,"text":"And this is what Richard Dawkins was on about"},{"time":264000,"text":"in his 1976 bestseller, \"The Selfish Gene.\""},{"time":267000,"text":"The information that is copied, he called the replicator."},{"time":271000,"text":"It selfishly copies."},{"time":273000,"text":"Not meaning it kind of sits around inside cells going, \"I want to get copied.\""},{"time":277000,"text":"But that it will get copied if it can,"},{"time":279000,"text":"regardless of the consequences."},{"time":282000,"text":"It doesn't care about the consequences because it can't,"},{"time":285000,"text":"because it's just information being copied."},{"time":288000,"text":"And he wanted to get away"},{"time":289000,"text":"from everybody thinking all the time about genes,"},{"time":292000,"text":"and so he said, \"Is there another replicator out there on the planet?\""},{"time":295000,"text":"Ah, yes, there is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297000,"text":"Look around you -- here will do, in this room."},{"time":300000,"text":"All around us, still clumsily drifting about"},{"time":303000,"text":"in its primeval soup of culture, is another replicator."},{"time":306000,"text":"Information that we copy from person to person, by imitation,"},{"time":311000,"text":"by language, by talking, by telling stories,"},{"time":313000,"text":"by wearing clothes, by doing things."},{"time":316000,"text":"This is information copied with variation and selection."},{"time":321000,"text":"This is design process going on."},{"time":324000,"text":"He wanted a name for the new replicator."},{"time":327000,"text":"So, he took the Greek word \"mimeme,\" which means that which is imitated."},{"time":331000,"text":"Remember that, that's the core definition:"},{"time":334000,"text":"that which is imitated."},{"time":335000,"text":"And abbreviated it to meme, just because it sounds good"},{"time":338000,"text":"and made a good meme, an effective spreading meme."},{"time":341000,"text":"So that's how the idea came about."},{"time":345000,"text":"It's important to stick with that definition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348000,"text":"The whole science of memetics is much maligned,"},{"time":352000,"text":"much misunderstood, much feared."},{"time":355000,"text":"But a lot of these problems can be avoided"},{"time":358000,"text":"by remembering the definition."},{"time":360000,"text":"A meme is not equivalent to an idea."},{"time":362000,"text":"It's not an idea. It's not equivalent to anything else, really."},{"time":364000,"text":"Stick with the definition."},{"time":366000,"text":"It's that which is imitated,"},{"time":368000,"text":"or information which is copied from person to person."},{"time":372000,"text":"So, let's see some memes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"Well, you sir, you've got those glasses hung around your neck"},{"time":376000,"text":"in that particularly fetching way."},{"time":378000,"text":"I wonder whether you invented that idea for yourself,"},{"time":380000,"text":"or copied it from someone else?"},{"time":382000,"text":"If you copied it from someone else, it's a meme."},{"time":385000,"text":"And what about, oh, I can't see any interesting memes here."},{"time":388000,"text":"All right everyone, who's got some interesting memes for me?"},{"time":391000,"text":"Oh, well, your earrings,"},{"time":393000,"text":"I don't suppose you invented the idea of earrings."},{"time":395000,"text":"You probably went out and bought them."},{"time":397000,"text":"There are plenty more in the shops."},{"time":399000,"text":"That's something that's passed on from person to person."},{"time":401000,"text":"All the stories that we're telling -- well, of course,"},{"time":404000,"text":"TED is a great meme-fest, masses of memes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408000,"text":"The way to think about memes, though,"},{"time":410000,"text":"is to think, why do they spread?"},{"time":412000,"text":"They're selfish information, they will get copied, if they can."},{"time":416000,"text":"But some of them will be copied because they're good,"},{"time":419000,"text":"or true, or useful, or beautiful."},{"time":421000,"text":"Some of them will be copied even though they're not."},{"time":423000,"text":"Some, it's quite hard to tell why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426000,"text":"There's one particular curious meme which I rather enjoy."},{"time":429000,"text":"And I'm glad to say, as I expected, I found it when I came here,"},{"time":432000,"text":"and I'm sure all of you found it, too."},{"time":434000,"text":"You go to your nice, posh, international hotel somewhere,"},{"time":438000,"text":"and you come in and you put down your clothes"},{"time":440000,"text":"and you go to the bathroom, and what do you see?"},{"time":443000,"text":"Audience: Bathroom soap."},{"time":444000,"text":"SB: Pardon?"},{"time":445000,"text":"Audience: Soap."},{"time":446000,"text":"SB: Soap, yeah. What else do you see?"},{"time":448000,"text":"Audience: (Inaudible)"},{"time":449000,"text":"SB: Mmm mmm."},{"time":450000,"text":"Audience: Sink, toilet!"},{"time":451000,"text":"SB: Sink, toilet, yes, these are all memes, they're all memes,"},{"time":453000,"text":"but they're sort of useful ones, and then there's this one."},{"time":456000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":460000,"text":"What is this one doing?"},{"time":462000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":463000,"text":"This has spread all over the world."},{"time":465000,"text":"It's not surprising that you all found it"},{"time":467000,"text":"when you arrived in your bathrooms here."},{"time":469000,"text":"But I took this photograph in a toilet at the back of a tent"},{"time":474000,"text":"in the eco-camp in the jungle in Assam."},{"time":476000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":478000,"text":"Who folded that thing up there, and why?"},{"time":481000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":482000,"text":"Some people get carried away."},{"time":484000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":488000,"text":"Other people are just lazy and make mistakes."},{"time":491000,"text":"Some hotels exploit the opportunity to put even more memes"},{"time":494000,"text":"with a little sticker."},{"time":496000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":497000,"text":"What is this all about?"},{"time":499000,"text":"I suppose it's there to tell you that somebody's"},{"time":501000,"text":"cleaned the place, and it's all lovely."},{"time":503000,"text":"And you know, actually, all it tells you is that another person"},{"time":506000,"text":"has potentially spread germs from place to place."},{"time":509000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":510000,"text":"So, think of it this way."},{"time":512000,"text":"Imagine a world full of brains"},{"time":514000,"text":"and far more memes than can possibly find homes."},{"time":517000,"text":"The memes are all trying to get copied --"},{"time":520000,"text":"trying, in inverted commas -- i.e.,"},{"time":523000,"text":"that's the shorthand for, if they can get copied, they will."},{"time":526000,"text":"They're using you and me as their propagating, copying machinery,"},{"time":532000,"text":"and we are the meme machines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535000,"text":"Now, why is this important?"},{"time":537000,"text":"Why is this useful, or what does it tell us?"},{"time":539000,"text":"It gives us a completely new view of human origins"},{"time":543000,"text":"and what it means to be human,"},{"time":544000,"text":"all conventional theories of cultural evolution,"},{"time":548000,"text":"of the origin of humans,"},{"time":550000,"text":"and what makes us so different from other species."},{"time":554000,"text":"All other theories explaining the big brain, and language, and tool use"},{"time":556000,"text":"and all these things that make us unique,"},{"time":558000,"text":"are based upon genes."},{"time":561000,"text":"Language must have been useful for the genes."},{"time":564000,"text":"Tool use must have enhanced our survival, mating and so on."},{"time":567000,"text":"It always comes back, as Richard Dawkins complained"},{"time":570000,"text":"all that long time ago, it always comes back to genes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573000,"text":"The point of memetics is to say, \"Oh no, it doesn't.\""},{"time":577000,"text":"There are two replicators now on this planet."},{"time":580000,"text":"From the moment that our ancestors,"},{"time":583000,"text":"perhaps two and a half million years ago or so,"},{"time":585000,"text":"began imitating, there was a new copying process."},{"time":589000,"text":"Copying with variation and selection."},{"time":591000,"text":"A new replicator was let loose, and it could never be --"},{"time":596000,"text":"right from the start -- it could never be"},{"time":597000,"text":"that human beings who let loose this new creature,"},{"time":602000,"text":"could just copy the useful, beautiful, true things,"},{"time":605000,"text":"and not copy the other things."},{"time":607000,"text":"While their brains were having an advantage from being able to copy --"},{"time":610000,"text":"lighting fires, keeping fires going, new techniques of hunting,"},{"time":615000,"text":"these kinds of things --"},{"time":617000,"text":"inevitably they were also copying putting feathers in their hair,"},{"time":620000,"text":"or wearing strange clothes, or painting their faces,"},{"time":622000,"text":"or whatever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623000,"text":"So, you get an arms race between the genes"},{"time":627000,"text":"which are trying to get the humans to have small economical brains"},{"time":631000,"text":"and not waste their time copying all this stuff,"},{"time":633000,"text":"and the memes themselves, like the sounds that people made and copied --"},{"time":638000,"text":"in other words, what turned out to be language --"},{"time":640000,"text":"competing to get the brains to get bigger and bigger."},{"time":643000,"text":"So, the big brain, on this theory, is driven by the memes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647000,"text":"This is why, in \"The Meme Machine,\" I called it memetic drive."},{"time":651000,"text":"As the memes evolve, as they inevitably must,"},{"time":654000,"text":"they drive a bigger brain that is better at copying the memes"},{"time":658000,"text":"that are doing the driving."},{"time":660000,"text":"This is why we've ended up with such peculiar brains,"},{"time":664000,"text":"that we like religion, and music, and art."},{"time":667000,"text":"Language is a parasite that we've adapted to,"},{"time":670000,"text":"not something that was there originally for our genes,"},{"time":672000,"text":"on this view."},{"time":674000,"text":"And like most parasites, it can begin dangerous,"},{"time":677000,"text":"but then it coevolves and adapts,"},{"time":680000,"text":"and we end up with a symbiotic relationship"},{"time":682000,"text":"with this new parasite."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683000,"text":"And so, from our perspective,"},{"time":685000,"text":"we don't realize that that's how it began."},{"time":688000,"text":"So, this is a view of what humans are."},{"time":691000,"text":"All other species on this planet are gene machines only,"},{"time":694000,"text":"they don't imitate at all well, hardly at all."},{"time":697000,"text":"We alone are gene machines and meme machines as well."},{"time":702000,"text":"The memes took a gene machine and turned it into a meme machine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706000,"text":"But that's not all."},{"time":708000,"text":"We have a new kind of memes now."},{"time":711000,"text":"I've been wondering for a long time,"},{"time":712000,"text":"since I've been thinking about memes a lot,"},{"time":714000,"text":"is there a difference between the memes that we copy --"},{"time":716000,"text":"the words we speak to each other,"},{"time":718000,"text":"the gestures we copy, the human things --"},{"time":720000,"text":"and all these technological things around us?"},{"time":722000,"text":"I have always, until now, called them all memes,"},{"time":726000,"text":"but I do honestly think now"},{"time":729000,"text":"we need a new word for technological memes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732000,"text":"Let's call them techno-memes or temes."},{"time":735000,"text":"Because the processes are getting different."},{"time":739000,"text":"We began, perhaps 5,000 years ago, with writing."},{"time":742000,"text":"We put the storage of memes out there on a clay tablet,"},{"time":750000,"text":"but in order to get true temes and true teme machines,"},{"time":752000,"text":"you need to get the variation, the selection and the copying,"},{"time":755000,"text":"all done outside of humans."},{"time":757000,"text":"And we're getting there."},{"time":759000,"text":"We're at this extraordinary point where we're nearly there,"},{"time":761000,"text":"that there are machines like that."},{"time":763000,"text":"And indeed, in the short time I've already been at TED,"},{"time":765000,"text":"I see we're even closer than I thought we were before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767000,"text":"So actually, now the temes are forcing our brains"},{"time":773000,"text":"to become more like teme machines."},{"time":775000,"text":"Our children are growing up very quickly learning to read,"},{"time":778000,"text":"learning to use machinery."},{"time":780000,"text":"We're going to have all kinds of implants,"},{"time":781000,"text":"drugs that force us to stay awake all the time."},{"time":784000,"text":"We'll think we're choosing these things,"},{"time":786000,"text":"but the temes are making us do it."},{"time":790000,"text":"So, we're at this cusp now"},{"time":791000,"text":"of having a third replicator on our planet."},{"time":796000,"text":"Now, what about what else is going on out there in the universe?"},{"time":801000,"text":"Is there anyone else out there?"},{"time":803000,"text":"People have been asking this question for a long time."},{"time":806000,"text":"We've been asking it here at TED already."},{"time":808000,"text":"In 1961, Frank Drake made his famous equation,"},{"time":812000,"text":"but I think he concentrated on the wrong things."},{"time":814000,"text":"It's been very productive, that equation."},{"time":816000,"text":"He wanted to estimate N,"},{"time":818000,"text":"the number of communicative civilizations out there in our galaxy,"},{"time":822000,"text":"and he included in there the rate of star formation,"},{"time":826000,"text":"the rate of planets, but crucially, intelligence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":830000,"text":"I think that's the wrong way to think about it."},{"time":834000,"text":"Intelligence appears all over the place, in all kinds of guises."},{"time":837000,"text":"Human intelligence is only one kind of a thing."},{"time":839000,"text":"But what's really important is the replicators you have"},{"time":842000,"text":"and the levels of replicators, one feeding on the one before."},{"time":846000,"text":"So, I would suggest that we don't think intelligence,"},{"time":851000,"text":"we think replicators."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853000,"text":"And on that basis, I've suggested a different kind of equation."},{"time":856000,"text":"A very simple equation."},{"time":858000,"text":"N, the same thing,"},{"time":860000,"text":"the number of communicative civilizations out there"},{"time":863000,"text":"[that] we might expect in our galaxy."},{"time":865000,"text":"Just start with the number of planets there are in our galaxy."},{"time":869000,"text":"The fraction of those which get a first replicator."},{"time":873000,"text":"The fraction of those that get the second replicator."},{"time":877000,"text":"The fraction of those that get the third replicator."},{"time":880000,"text":"Because it's only the third replicator that's going to reach out --"},{"time":883000,"text":"sending information, sending probes, getting out there,"},{"time":886000,"text":"and communicating with anywhere else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":888000,"text":"OK, so if we take that equation,"},{"time":891000,"text":"why haven't we heard from anybody out there?"},{"time":896000,"text":"Because every step is dangerous."},{"time":900000,"text":"Getting a new replicator is dangerous."},{"time":903000,"text":"You can pull through, we have pulled through,"},{"time":905000,"text":"but it's dangerous."},{"time":907000,"text":"Take the first step, as soon as life appeared on this earth."},{"time":910000,"text":"We may take the Gaian view."},{"time":912000,"text":"I loved Peter Ward's talk yesterday -- it's not Gaian all the time."},{"time":915000,"text":"Actually, life forms produce things that kill themselves."},{"time":918000,"text":"Well, we did pull through on this planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":921000,"text":"But then, a long time later, billions of years later,"},{"time":923000,"text":"we got the second replicator, the memes."},{"time":926000,"text":"That was dangerous, all right."},{"time":928000,"text":"Think of the big brain."},{"time":930000,"text":"How many mothers do we have here?"},{"time":933000,"text":"You know all about big brains."},{"time":935000,"text":"They are dangerous to give birth to,"},{"time":937000,"text":"are agonizing to give birth to."},{"time":939000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":941000,"text":"My cat gave birth to four kittens, purring all the time."},{"time":943000,"text":"Ah, mm -- slightly different."},{"time":945000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":947000,"text":"But not only is it painful, it kills lots of babies,"},{"time":950000,"text":"it kills lots of mothers,"},{"time":952000,"text":"and it's very expensive to produce."},{"time":954000,"text":"The genes are forced into producing all this myelin,"},{"time":956000,"text":"all the fat to myelinate the brain."},{"time":958000,"text":"Do you know, sitting here,"},{"time":960000,"text":"your brain is using about 20 percent of your body's energy output"},{"time":964000,"text":"for two percent of your body weight?"},{"time":966000,"text":"It's a really expensive organ to run."},{"time":968000,"text":"Why? Because it's producing the memes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":970000,"text":"Now, it could have killed us off. It could have killed us off,"},{"time":974000,"text":"and maybe it nearly did, but you see, we don't know."},{"time":976000,"text":"But maybe it nearly did."},{"time":978000,"text":"Has it been tried before?"},{"time":979000,"text":"What about all those other species?"},{"time":981000,"text":"Louise Leakey talked yesterday"},{"time":983000,"text":"about how we're the only one in this branch left."},{"time":986000,"text":"What happened to the others?"},{"time":988000,"text":"Could it be that this experiment in imitation,"},{"time":990000,"text":"this experiment in a second replicator,"},{"time":992000,"text":"is dangerous enough to kill people off?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":996000,"text":"Well, we did pull through, and we adapted."},{"time":998000,"text":"But now, we're hitting, as I've just described,"},{"time":1001000,"text":"we're hitting the third replicator point."},{"time":1003000,"text":"And this is even more dangerous --"},{"time":1006000,"text":"well, it's dangerous again."},{"time":1008000,"text":"Why? Because the temes are selfish replicators"},{"time":1012000,"text":"and they don't care about us, or our planet, or anything else."},{"time":1015000,"text":"They're just information, why would they?"},{"time":1019000,"text":"They are using us to suck up the planet's resources"},{"time":1021000,"text":"to produce more computers,"},{"time":1023000,"text":"and more of all these amazing things we're hearing about here at TED."},{"time":1026000,"text":"Don't think, \"Oh, we created the Internet for our own benefit.\""},{"time":1030000,"text":"That's how it seems to us."},{"time":1032000,"text":"Think, temes spreading because they must."},{"time":1036000,"text":"We are the old machines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1038000,"text":"Now, are we going to pull through?"},{"time":1040000,"text":"What's going to happen?"},{"time":1042000,"text":"What does it mean to pull through?"},{"time":1044000,"text":"Well, there are kind of two ways of pulling through."},{"time":1047000,"text":"One that is obviously happening all around us now,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"is that the temes turn us into teme machines,"},{"time":1053000,"text":"with these implants, with the drugs,"},{"time":1055000,"text":"with us merging with the technology."},{"time":1058000,"text":"And why would they do that?"},{"time":1060000,"text":"Because we are self-replicating."},{"time":1062000,"text":"We have babies."},{"time":1064000,"text":"We make new ones, and so it's convenient to piggyback on us,"},{"time":1067000,"text":"because we're not yet at the stage on this planet"},{"time":1071000,"text":"where the other option is viable."},{"time":1073000,"text":"Although it's closer, I heard this morning,"},{"time":1075000,"text":"it's closer than I thought it was."},{"time":1077000,"text":"Where the teme machines themselves will replicate themselves."},{"time":1080000,"text":"That way, it wouldn't matter if the planet's climate"},{"time":1084000,"text":"was utterly destabilized,"},{"time":1086000,"text":"and it was no longer possible for humans to live here."},{"time":1088000,"text":"Because those teme machines, they wouldn't need --"},{"time":1090000,"text":"they're not squishy, wet, oxygen-breathing,"},{"time":1092000,"text":"warmth-requiring creatures."},{"time":1095000,"text":"They could carry on without us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1097000,"text":"So, those are the two possibilities."},{"time":1100000,"text":"The second, I don't think we're that close."},{"time":1104000,"text":"It's coming, but we're not there yet."},{"time":1106000,"text":"The first, it's coming too."},{"time":1108000,"text":"But the damage that is already being done"},{"time":1111000,"text":"to the planet is showing us how dangerous the third point is,"},{"time":1116000,"text":"that third danger point, getting a third replicator."},{"time":1120000,"text":"And will we get through this third danger point,"},{"time":1122000,"text":"like we got through the second and like we got through the first?"},{"time":1126000,"text":"Maybe we will, maybe we won't."},{"time":1128000,"text":"I have no idea."},{"time":1135000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1146000,"text":"Chris Anderson: That was an incredible talk."},{"time":1148000,"text":"SB: Thank you. I scared myself."},{"time":1150000,"text":"CA: (Laughter)"}]}]}